WEBVTT

00:00:02.720 --> 00:00:05.439
- <i>Previously on</i> The O.C.<i>:</i>
- Can we just start over?

00:00:06.400 --> 00:00:07.594
- Wait.
- Don't you want to?

00:00:07.760 --> 00:00:09.193
No.

00:00:09.840 --> 00:00:11.068
- Ryan.
- Theresa.

00:00:11.240 --> 00:00:13.310
- You ever think about coming home?
- Sometimes.

00:00:13.480 --> 00:00:15.118
I know I shouldn't be here.

00:00:15.440 --> 00:00:16.668
Would you like to come in?

00:00:16.840 --> 00:00:19.513
It's always been you, Summer.
You're undeniable.

00:00:19.800 --> 00:00:24.032
I'm a man now. I had sex with a girl.
Summer, to be more specific.

00:00:24.200 --> 00:00:25.918
Hi, Marissa. Theresa.

00:00:27.640 --> 00:00:29.551
Okay. Bye.

00:00:39.600 --> 00:00:43.718
So you and Marissa, you guys broken up?
You guys taking a break? What's the deal?

00:00:43.880 --> 00:00:46.838
I don't know.
We're just not seeing each other.

00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:50.879
Except you will see each other, at school
every day for the next couple years.

00:00:51.040 --> 00:00:54.794
Right. Well, we'll just
go back to being friends.

00:00:54.960 --> 00:00:57.030
When were you guys ever friends?

00:00:57.200 --> 00:01:01.352
Was it when you were beating up her
boyfriend? Or spooning in a Tijuana motel?

00:01:01.520 --> 00:01:04.432
- Is that when you were friends?
- Doesn't mean we can't be friends.

00:01:04.600 --> 00:01:05.919
I don't know.

00:01:06.360 --> 00:01:07.588
Think I'll see her today?

00:01:07.760 --> 00:01:08.909
Friends, Coop?

00:01:09.080 --> 00:01:12.789
What are you guys gonna do together?
Lift weights? Try on wife-beaters?

00:01:12.960 --> 00:01:15.474
Sorry. Guys like Ryan
aren't friends with girls.

00:01:15.640 --> 00:01:18.712
I don't wanna just be his friend.
But after the whole Oliver thing...

00:01:18.880 --> 00:01:21.838
...I guess I need to show him
he can trust me.

00:01:22.960 --> 00:01:25.520
Who knows if he'll
even wanna be friends.

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:27.911
- So how goes it with Seth?
- Weird.

00:01:28.080 --> 00:01:30.719
In public, he's like this huge geek
who mumbles.

00:01:30.880 --> 00:01:34.236
I don't even know what he's saying half
the time. But behind closed doors...

00:01:34.400 --> 00:01:37.312
...underneath the sheets,
he's like the anti-Cohen.

00:01:37.480 --> 00:01:39.198
You think I'll have to see him today?

00:01:39.360 --> 00:01:41.999
I think me and Summer are finally
over the hump, by the way.

00:01:42.160 --> 00:01:44.435
So to speak. I just hope, man...

00:01:44.600 --> 00:01:47.319
...that she can keep it in her trousers
when she sees me today.

00:01:47.480 --> 00:01:50.153
She'll probably have her little paws
all over me.

00:01:50.720 --> 00:01:53.359
That's probably her now,
a little phone sex.

00:01:53.880 --> 00:01:55.916
Who do I know from the 909?

00:01:56.080 --> 00:01:57.832
Nobody.

00:01:59.280 --> 00:02:00.554
- Hello?
- <i>Ryan?</i>

00:02:00.720 --> 00:02:02.517
Hi, it's Theresa.

00:02:02.680 --> 00:02:06.434
- Yeah, Seth's mom gave me this number.
- Hey. How are you? Everything okay?

00:02:06.600 --> 00:02:08.397
Yeah, fine.

00:02:08.560 --> 00:02:11.632
- I'm actually coming out there today.
- You are? How come?

00:02:11.800 --> 00:02:14.758
- I mean, for work?
- Yeah...

00:02:14.920 --> 00:02:17.150
...but they can't make us
work all the time, right?

00:02:17.320 --> 00:02:20.995
- I was thinking we could hang out tonight.
- Tonight? Sure.

00:02:21.280 --> 00:02:25.512
- Don't sound so excited.
- I am. I'm just a little surprised, that's all.

00:02:25.680 --> 00:02:28.831
Oh, you know me, full of surprises.
So I'll come by after dinner.

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:30.956
Yeah, sounds good. See you then.

00:02:31.560 --> 00:02:32.879
Hey, baby. Who's that?

00:02:33.040 --> 00:02:34.871
Wrong number.

00:02:37.280 --> 00:02:40.556
That was Theresa.
She's in town, wants to hang out.

00:02:40.800 --> 00:02:42.631
As a friend.

00:02:43.120 --> 00:02:45.350
Well, first Marissa, then Theresa.

00:02:45.520 --> 00:02:47.511
Who knew Ryan Atwood was so friendly?

00:03:28.120 --> 00:03:29.792
- Summer.
- Cohen.

00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:31.757
- Ryan.
- Hi.

00:03:32.400 --> 00:03:35.358
- Summer. Can we talk?
- Hey, Brad, what's up?

00:03:35.520 --> 00:03:36.714
Brad.

00:03:36.880 --> 00:03:39.519
Dude, I didn't recognize you
out of the Speedo.

00:03:39.720 --> 00:03:42.473
Not that I'd recognize you
in a Speedo, but...

00:03:42.640 --> 00:03:44.949
Okay. Come on.

00:03:45.400 --> 00:03:47.118
Jeez.

00:03:50.480 --> 00:03:53.392
- So how are you?
- I'm...

00:03:55.520 --> 00:03:57.715
I'm late. See you.

00:04:00.160 --> 00:04:03.550
So we're doing a fundraiser for the team,
a kissing booth.

00:04:03.720 --> 00:04:06.154
I'm gonna be the guy,
and we're looking for a girl...

00:04:06.320 --> 00:04:09.153
...who's comfortable being paid
to make out with a bunch of guys.

00:04:09.320 --> 00:04:12.471
- Naturally, I thought of you.
- Really? You thought of me?

00:04:12.720 --> 00:04:15.632
God. Totally. I mean, why not?

00:04:15.800 --> 00:04:17.313
- Thanks, Summer.
- Sure.

00:04:17.600 --> 00:04:20.637
He talked to you like I wasn't there.
Does he know we're going out?

00:04:20.800 --> 00:04:22.518
It's not like he wants to kiss me.

00:04:22.680 --> 00:04:25.513
He just wants me to kiss
a bunch of other dudes for money.

00:04:25.680 --> 00:04:27.671
I'll see you tonight. My place?

00:04:27.840 --> 00:04:29.239
You can help me practice.

00:04:32.880 --> 00:04:34.871
- Anna.
- So you guys are together now?

00:04:35.040 --> 00:04:37.918
Well, that didn't take long, did it?

00:04:38.080 --> 00:04:39.513
Yeah, Summer and I are...

00:04:39.680 --> 00:04:41.033
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

00:04:41.200 --> 00:04:44.033
I mean, I did see it coming.
It's the reason I broke up with you.

00:04:45.960 --> 00:04:48.474
- Hey, how was Pittsburgh?
- It was good to be home.

00:04:48.640 --> 00:04:52.349
Pittsburgh's also the home
of Andy Warhol, Mr. Rogers and ketchup.

00:04:52.520 --> 00:04:54.272
- You can't compete with that.
- You can't.

00:04:54.560 --> 00:04:57.552
Yeah, it was really great.
I got a tuna melt at my favorite diner...

00:04:57.720 --> 00:05:00.280
...and I saw <i>Some Kind of Wonderful</i>
at the midnight movie...

00:05:00.440 --> 00:05:03.273
...and hung out with all my friends.
It was really nice.

00:05:03.520 --> 00:05:05.829
Guess I didn't realize
how much I missed them.

00:05:07.440 --> 00:05:09.431
Hey, Dad.
You wanted to see me?

00:05:09.680 --> 00:05:11.875
Kiki, we got a problem.

00:05:12.120 --> 00:05:15.317
- Uncle Shaun was arrested last night.
- You're kidding. For what?

00:05:15.480 --> 00:05:18.119
He was drunk, stumbled into
another guest's room at the St. Regis.

00:05:18.640 --> 00:05:20.949
He's been stumbling around drunk
since you met him...

00:05:21.120 --> 00:05:24.078
...which was in a bar.
I'll have someone in Legal handle it.

00:05:24.240 --> 00:05:27.277
- I was thinking you might ask Sandy.
- Very funny.

00:05:27.440 --> 00:05:30.238
He knows people at the DA's office.
He can make this go away.

00:05:30.400 --> 00:05:32.152
- He'll never do it.
- Why not?

00:05:32.320 --> 00:05:35.073
- Because it would be a favor to me?
- Pretty much. Yeah.

00:05:35.240 --> 00:05:37.435
You could tell him
it would mean a lot to you.

00:05:38.080 --> 00:05:40.310
Actually, it would mean a lot to me.

00:05:40.480 --> 00:05:42.948
But if you want Sandy's help
after all these years...

00:05:43.120 --> 00:05:47.238
...then you need to ask him,
because that would mean a lot to Sandy.

00:05:50.360 --> 00:05:52.635
- No.
- You should see these two guys.

00:05:52.800 --> 00:05:55.678
- Oh, come on.
- Honestly, it was unbelievable.

00:05:55.840 --> 00:05:57.159
I swear to God.

00:05:57.320 --> 00:05:59.356
- Hi.
- Hi.

00:06:00.040 --> 00:06:03.032
So this is you and Summer
being a couple?

00:06:04.640 --> 00:06:06.915
- Ain't love grand?
- I can really sense the bond.

00:06:07.080 --> 00:06:10.231
It's like, your closeness,
it's overwhelming.

00:06:10.400 --> 00:06:11.958
Oh, my gosh. Wait.

00:06:12.120 --> 00:06:14.190
Is it last fall already?

00:06:14.360 --> 00:06:17.670
- Come on, she's totally ignoring you.
- Anna, she's not ignoring me.

00:06:17.840 --> 00:06:21.594
Summer just has her priorities in order.
You know how she feels about charity.

00:06:24.800 --> 00:06:27.519
- Yes?
- Yeah. Good luck with that.

00:06:41.000 --> 00:06:42.877
Mrs. Cooper.

00:06:43.040 --> 00:06:45.759
- What are you doing here?
- Parent-teacher conference.

00:06:45.920 --> 00:06:49.435
- It's good to see you.
- It's good to see you too.

00:06:50.080 --> 00:06:53.117
Really good. You... I mean...
God, you look good.

00:06:53.280 --> 00:06:56.875
Luke, I'm Marissa's mother.
You're a student at this school.

00:06:57.600 --> 00:07:00.831
- We can't do this.
- You mean it's over?

00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:02.797
No, I mean in the hallway.

00:07:02.960 --> 00:07:04.712
I'll see you tonight.

00:07:05.280 --> 00:07:06.759
- Hey, Julie.
- Jimmy, hi.

00:07:06.920 --> 00:07:09.150
- You remember Luke.
- Who could forget?

00:07:09.320 --> 00:07:10.799
- Luke.
- Hey, Mr. Cooper.

00:07:10.960 --> 00:07:14.714
I'm glad you're here. I didn't want to go
to Dr. Kim's office alone. She scares me.

00:07:14.880 --> 00:07:18.077
Okay, well, goodbye, Mrs. Cooper.
And Mr. Cooper.

00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:20.553
I'll see you.

00:07:20.720 --> 00:07:22.278
Both.

00:07:25.560 --> 00:07:27.551
Have a good day.

00:07:32.840 --> 00:07:35.559
Hey, I'm sorry about this morning.
That...

00:07:35.720 --> 00:07:37.915
- It shouldn't have to be...
- Like this?

00:07:39.040 --> 00:07:41.713
I was just sort of hoping
we could be friends, you know?

00:07:41.880 --> 00:07:45.111
- I mean, as long as that's okay with you.
- Yeah. No, we should hang out.

00:07:45.760 --> 00:07:48.069
Okay.
What are you doing tonight?

00:07:48.520 --> 00:07:51.557
- Tonight's no good.
- It's okay. We don't have to do this.

00:07:51.720 --> 00:07:53.597
What about after school?

00:07:53.760 --> 00:07:55.830
Actually, after school's good.
It's better...

00:07:56.000 --> 00:07:58.798
...because I'm supposed to have dinner
with my dad. Your place?

00:07:58.960 --> 00:08:00.916
- Yeah, see you then.
- Cool.

00:08:08.960 --> 00:08:10.359
Well...

00:08:10.520 --> 00:08:14.115
...the restaurant's coming along, Sandy.
At this rate, you'll be open by 2008.

00:08:14.280 --> 00:08:16.316
And there goes my appetite.
Caleb, hello.

00:08:17.120 --> 00:08:19.714
- What the hell is that?
- It's my mother's meat loaf.

00:08:19.880 --> 00:08:21.677
- God, your mother's here?
- Her recipe is.

00:08:21.840 --> 00:08:25.435
- We're trying out a chef. You want some?
- The sight of your mother's meat loaf...

00:08:25.600 --> 00:08:27.989
...has turned me into a vegetarian.

00:08:28.160 --> 00:08:31.948
I know you're a big fan of the pop-in, but
is there another reason why you're here?

00:08:32.120 --> 00:08:34.236
I've come to ask a favor.

00:08:34.480 --> 00:08:35.833
I'm sorry, what did you say?

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:39.197
- You didn't hear me?
- I heard you. I want you to say it again.

00:08:39.360 --> 00:08:42.477
- A friend is in trouble. I want you to help.
- I didn't know you had friends.

00:08:42.640 --> 00:08:45.074
- It's Bill Shaughnessy.
- Uncle Shaun.

00:08:45.240 --> 00:08:49.119
You pay Uncle Shaun to be your friend.
I guess he qualifies. What did he do?

00:08:49.280 --> 00:08:52.158
He was drinking, stumbled into
someone else's hotel room.

00:08:52.320 --> 00:08:55.596
They called security,
and now it's a legal matter.

00:08:55.760 --> 00:08:59.355
- You've got lawyers at your beck and call.
- He came to me as a friend.

00:08:59.520 --> 00:09:01.988
I want it handled like a friend.
Quietly.

00:09:02.160 --> 00:09:04.628
By someone who has a relationship
with the DA's office?

00:09:04.800 --> 00:09:08.679
I'm asking you.
I've known Shaun for over 40 years.

00:09:08.840 --> 00:09:10.558
It would mean a lot to me.

00:09:12.160 --> 00:09:14.913
- Did Kirsten tell you to say that?
- She thinks you'll say no.

00:09:15.080 --> 00:09:17.275
My wife knows me pretty well.

00:09:17.440 --> 00:09:19.510
But, you know,
sometimes I like to surprise her.

00:09:19.680 --> 00:09:23.195
I don't want her to go and get all
conceited and stuff, you know?

00:09:23.360 --> 00:09:26.636
You have a copy of the police report?
Now, I'm not saying that I'll do it.

00:09:26.800 --> 00:09:31.157
I'm saying that I'll look at the report,
I'll make some calls and then we'll see.

00:09:34.360 --> 00:09:36.828
- Got any more of that meat loaf?
- Maybe.

00:09:37.680 --> 00:09:40.797
Well, that was a relief. Dr. Kim seems
to think Marissa's doing well.

00:09:40.960 --> 00:09:43.269
I was sure she was gonna revoke
my license to parent.

00:09:43.440 --> 00:09:45.908
You know, Jimmy,
I don't think I ever thanked you.

00:09:46.520 --> 00:09:49.717
That's not true. You've thanked me
for alienating the community...

00:09:49.880 --> 00:09:52.792
...destroying the family.
- For doing a wonderful job with Marissa.

00:09:53.160 --> 00:09:55.515
I'm serious.
Listening to you in that meeting...

00:09:55.680 --> 00:09:59.832
...you're totally involved in her life.
- You and Caleb must be doing really well.

00:10:00.440 --> 00:10:03.955
- Why would you say that?
- Because you're being so...

00:10:04.120 --> 00:10:06.156
...nice.
- Well, actually...

00:10:06.320 --> 00:10:09.392
...Caleb and I aren't
seeing each other anymore.

00:10:09.560 --> 00:10:11.039
And I'm much happier.

00:10:12.680 --> 00:10:16.958
And to think, you've spent a lifetime
wanting to be rich and married...

00:10:17.120 --> 00:10:20.157
...when what agrees with you most
is being poor and alone.

00:10:22.080 --> 00:10:24.548
Isn't it better when we're alone?
Just the two of us?

00:10:29.000 --> 00:10:31.673
- Why did you ignore me at school today?
- I didn't ignore you.

00:10:33.280 --> 00:10:35.669
Okay, maybe a little.

00:10:35.840 --> 00:10:38.718
I just... I want our relationship
to be private, okay?

00:10:38.880 --> 00:10:41.075
I don't like other people
knowing my business.

00:10:41.240 --> 00:10:43.834
- Why not?
- Because it's none of their business.

00:10:44.040 --> 00:10:47.112
Look, there's, like, pressure...

00:10:47.280 --> 00:10:50.590
...and scrutiny in the spotlight.
- What spotlight?

00:10:50.760 --> 00:10:53.593
When has being in the public eye
ever helped a relationship?

00:10:53.760 --> 00:10:57.070
Sure, we're this week's hottest couple,
but then the world gets sick of it.

00:10:57.240 --> 00:11:00.152
The shopping sprees, the strip clubs.
People turn against us, okay?

00:11:00.320 --> 00:11:02.231
"How many Juicy sweat suits
does she need?"

00:11:02.400 --> 00:11:06.234
"That goatee is so mid-'90s." Pretty soon,
the movie bombs and the wedding is off!

00:11:07.560 --> 00:11:10.711
But I'm not gonna let that
happen to us, because, Cohen...

00:11:10.880 --> 00:11:12.313
...what we have is special.

00:11:12.640 --> 00:11:14.392
Summer...

00:11:15.120 --> 00:11:18.237
...that's maybe just...

00:11:24.960 --> 00:11:26.757
- Guess I'm not very good.
- Yeah.

00:11:26.920 --> 00:11:29.514
Want a rematch?
Because I couldn't possibly get any worse.

00:11:29.680 --> 00:11:32.752
No, I should probably
start on my homework.

00:11:32.920 --> 00:11:36.549
Oh, yeah, me too.
I mean, my dad's probably waiting.

00:11:37.480 --> 00:11:41.075
- Is this...? I don't know, are we...?
- Why...? Why is this weird?

00:11:41.240 --> 00:11:43.834
- It shouldn't be.
- We used to hang out all the time and...

00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:45.797
Make out?

00:11:46.320 --> 00:11:48.311
- We could always fight about Luke.
- Or Oliver.

00:11:51.680 --> 00:11:54.478
Sorry. I just...

00:11:56.240 --> 00:11:57.434
Hey, Ryan.

00:11:58.400 --> 00:11:59.992
Hey, Marissa.

00:12:02.400 --> 00:12:04.755
I'm early. Sorry.
I'll go and come back later.

00:12:04.920 --> 00:12:06.592
It's okay.
We weren't doing anything.

00:12:06.760 --> 00:12:09.479
Yeah, I was just leaving.
He's got a lot of homework.

00:12:09.920 --> 00:12:11.194
Good to see you, Theresa.

00:12:11.600 --> 00:12:13.431
It's nice to see you too.

00:12:15.800 --> 00:12:17.552
The ninja game?

00:12:17.720 --> 00:12:19.836
You're dead now.

00:12:23.880 --> 00:12:25.916
Considering he is your "Uncle" Shaun...

00:12:26.080 --> 00:12:28.310
...don't you think it's weird
we have never met?

00:12:28.960 --> 00:12:31.758
He's not really my uncle.

00:12:31.960 --> 00:12:34.394
- And he pretty much works all the time.
- Doing what?

00:12:34.560 --> 00:12:35.959
He's a consultant.

00:12:36.120 --> 00:12:38.918
Could you please be a little more vague?

00:12:39.080 --> 00:12:40.593
He knows people.

00:12:40.760 --> 00:12:43.115
You did it.
That was more vague.

00:12:43.280 --> 00:12:46.317
The guys at the permit office,
the union guys.

00:12:46.480 --> 00:12:48.550
He's our liaison.

00:12:51.240 --> 00:12:54.312
Well, I looked over the police report,
I put in a few calls...

00:12:54.960 --> 00:12:58.157
...and I'm sure I'll hear something back
before we get together tonight.

00:12:58.320 --> 00:13:00.515
- Thank you.
- Overexposure, Ryan...

00:13:00.680 --> 00:13:03.638
...it's a major source of conflict
in new relationships.

00:13:03.800 --> 00:13:06.837
"Summereth." "Sethummer."
You understand what I'm saying?

00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:09.833
- No. No. That's normal.
- Ryan, your friend Theresa called.

00:13:10.160 --> 00:13:13.436
- I'd like to meet Theresa.
- Yeah, she'd like to meet you guys.

00:13:13.600 --> 00:13:16.273
- What's she doing here?
- Taking a semester off, making money.

00:13:16.440 --> 00:13:19.750
Catering a tennis tournament.
Her mom got laid off.

00:13:19.920 --> 00:13:22.480
So she's out here a while.
Does Marissa know? I'm curious.

00:13:22.800 --> 00:13:24.916
They kind of bumped into each other.

00:13:25.080 --> 00:13:27.992
Look at you, the friend guy.
Bringing friends together.

00:13:28.160 --> 00:13:30.037
- I sense sarcasm.
- You're perceptive.

00:13:30.240 --> 00:13:33.994
This mysterious <i>caliente</i> female from
your past just shows up out of nowhere...

00:13:34.160 --> 00:13:37.914
...with all this time on her hands
and no one to spend it with but you.

00:13:38.080 --> 00:13:41.516
- Marissa okay with this?
- She's fine. They're back to being friends.

00:13:41.680 --> 00:13:43.352
So when were they ever friends?

00:13:50.640 --> 00:13:52.232
You are so beautiful, you know that?

00:13:54.240 --> 00:13:55.434
You're very sweet.

00:13:57.520 --> 00:14:00.751
- I wish we could stay here forever.
- Why?

00:14:00.920 --> 00:14:04.708
We got everything we need here.
We got our bed. We got our cable.

00:14:04.880 --> 00:14:06.677
We got each other.

00:14:07.160 --> 00:14:09.674
- This place is awesome.
- It's not awesome.

00:14:09.840 --> 00:14:12.274
It's $ 79 a night.

00:14:12.800 --> 00:14:16.236
I gotta motor.
I don't wanna be late for homeroom.

00:14:16.440 --> 00:14:18.158
You have homeroom.

00:14:18.320 --> 00:14:20.709
Right. Because you're in high school.

00:14:20.880 --> 00:14:22.438
And you're only 18.

00:14:27.280 --> 00:14:29.919
Kaitlin, are you okay?

00:14:30.760 --> 00:14:32.159
You're in front of the house?

00:14:32.320 --> 00:14:35.869
Chester's mom was supposed to pick you
up at Grandma's and take you to school.

00:14:37.120 --> 00:14:39.156
Your diorama.

00:14:39.520 --> 00:14:42.034
Yeah, I think it's
in the living room, honey.

00:14:42.200 --> 00:14:45.510
Okay, just wait there with Grandma.
I'll be there as soon as I can.

00:14:45.800 --> 00:14:47.199
Okay. See you soon.

00:14:49.680 --> 00:14:51.750
- See you tonight?
- Oh, Luke.

00:14:51.920 --> 00:14:54.593
Motels, homerooms, dioramas.

00:14:54.760 --> 00:14:58.639
- This is not the stuff of great romance.
- But, Mrs...

00:14:58.960 --> 00:15:00.678
Julie.

00:15:01.800 --> 00:15:03.597
I'm sorry.

00:15:06.240 --> 00:15:08.629
- No worries.
- Good.

00:15:34.600 --> 00:15:36.033
Hey.

00:15:36.240 --> 00:15:38.708
- You mind if...?
- No.

00:15:39.120 --> 00:15:40.519
Thanks.

00:15:43.160 --> 00:15:45.515
- So, sorry about...
- Sorry I was such a...

00:15:46.920 --> 00:15:49.480
- I should've told you she was coming.
- You didn't have to.

00:15:49.640 --> 00:15:52.200
But you could've.
I mean, now that we're friends, right?

00:15:52.360 --> 00:15:55.830
- Right.
- So you and Theresa...?

00:15:56.320 --> 00:15:59.073
- We're friends.
- And she's back in town for...?

00:15:59.240 --> 00:16:01.800
Work. She's staying
till the end of the week.

00:16:02.760 --> 00:16:06.469
- Where's she staying?
- The motel by the pier.

00:16:06.640 --> 00:16:08.710
The Seashell? Sea Monkey?

00:16:09.160 --> 00:16:11.549
- The Mermaid.
- Right.

00:16:11.720 --> 00:16:14.951
- Next week we could have that rematch.
- Think you're up for it?

00:16:15.120 --> 00:16:18.078
Hey, what I lack in nunchaku,
I make up for in saber.

00:16:19.560 --> 00:16:20.993
So...

00:16:21.200 --> 00:16:23.475
...did you talk to Summer yesterday?
- Yeah.

00:16:23.640 --> 00:16:26.916
- Oh, yeah?
- We talked about school...

00:16:27.080 --> 00:16:28.911
...and sports and the weather.

00:16:29.080 --> 00:16:31.878
But if you're referring to the part
where she's ashamed of me, no.

00:16:32.040 --> 00:16:33.598
Didn't get to that.

00:16:34.600 --> 00:16:38.513
Were you gonna say something?
Something very wise and helpful, Anna?

00:16:38.920 --> 00:16:42.151
- No.
- You got nothing? No advice at all for me?

00:16:42.320 --> 00:16:44.754
- I feel like you did.
- Why do I do this?

00:16:44.920 --> 00:16:47.195
Because you're so wise, Anna.
You can't not.

00:16:47.360 --> 00:16:50.318
All right, fine.
Look, you have to take a stand, all right?

00:16:50.480 --> 00:16:52.357
You can't let her get away with it.

00:16:52.560 --> 00:16:54.596
Otherwise she has something
to be ashamed of...

00:16:54.760 --> 00:16:57.115
...because then her boyfriend
is a coward.

00:17:00.360 --> 00:17:04.148
I'm just going to help with the kissing
booth, you know, because I love to help.

00:17:05.680 --> 00:17:08.035
Right, coward. Got it.

00:17:11.680 --> 00:17:14.478
Hope you don't mind.
I let myself in through the back.

00:17:14.640 --> 00:17:16.949
It's what you do.
Famous Uncle Shaun.

00:17:17.240 --> 00:17:20.516
Here. Famous Grouse.

00:17:20.680 --> 00:17:23.353
I haven't seen a bottle of this
since Bob Mitchum passed.

00:17:23.520 --> 00:17:26.318
- You knew Robert Mitchum?
- Yeah. He and his wife Dorothy...

00:17:26.480 --> 00:17:30.758
...they used to have a place over there
on Linda Isle.

00:17:31.280 --> 00:17:35.239
That was their favorite booth.
Sunday dinners. Chicken parm.

00:17:35.400 --> 00:17:39.109
I'm partial to the parm myself,
and a lover of blended Scotch.

00:17:39.600 --> 00:17:42.876
And Caleb keeps saying
you have no redeeming qualities.

00:17:45.200 --> 00:17:47.998
So I read the police report.
I just have a couple of questions.

00:17:48.160 --> 00:17:51.277
This fellow who's pressing charges,
he's in the construction business.

00:17:51.440 --> 00:17:54.079
- Really?
- Yeah. Yeah, he's a lumber supplier...

00:17:54.240 --> 00:17:58.518
...one of the biggest in the country.
In fact, he was in town on a negotiation...

00:17:58.680 --> 00:18:00.875
...with one of the Newport Group's
chief rivals.

00:18:01.160 --> 00:18:02.957
- Imagine that.
- Yeah, I'm guessing...

00:18:03.640 --> 00:18:06.313
...that in that room
that you accidentally stumbled into...

00:18:06.480 --> 00:18:08.311
...were documents
containing information...

00:18:08.480 --> 00:18:11.517
...that would be very valuable
to somebody like Caleb.

00:18:11.680 --> 00:18:14.956
- You think?
- You expect me or the DA's office...

00:18:15.120 --> 00:18:19.716
...to believe a bellyful of liquor or a wild
coincidence would put you in that room?

00:18:20.720 --> 00:18:22.312
You were there for Caleb.

00:18:22.480 --> 00:18:24.710
That's an interesting theory.

00:18:24.880 --> 00:18:29.431
And one I, you know, hope you don't
explore too much, because...

00:18:29.600 --> 00:18:33.718
What is it, "Sandy"? You know, Caleb
and I have been friends for many years.

00:18:33.880 --> 00:18:36.713
And if I were to sit down with the DA...

00:18:36.880 --> 00:18:40.236
...there's no telling
what we might talk about.

00:18:47.920 --> 00:18:49.512
- So, what do you think?
- It's good.

00:18:51.440 --> 00:18:54.591
- They call them Balboa Bars.
- It's just ice cream.

00:18:54.760 --> 00:18:56.796
No such thing
as just ice cream in Newport.

00:18:56.960 --> 00:19:00.748
Like, instead of car washes,
they have auto spas.

00:19:01.000 --> 00:19:03.673
Dogs have daycare.
Fashion Island has valet parking.

00:19:03.840 --> 00:19:05.558
It's a weird place.

00:19:05.720 --> 00:19:07.995
Still, it's beautiful.

00:19:08.160 --> 00:19:11.755
I can see why you wanna live here,
start over.

00:19:12.000 --> 00:19:14.275
Is that why you came back here?
Start over?

00:19:15.760 --> 00:19:18.320
No, I couldn't.

00:19:18.680 --> 00:19:20.750
I've got my mom to think about.

00:19:20.920 --> 00:19:23.673
My brother. And Eddie.

00:19:25.480 --> 00:19:26.879
You guys are still...?

00:19:27.040 --> 00:19:31.079
We're taking some time apart. You know,
to see if we really belong together.

00:19:31.680 --> 00:19:35.150
- What about you and Marissa?
- Kind of the same thing, I guess.

00:19:35.320 --> 00:19:38.551
We're trying to be friends,
but it hasn't exactly been easy.

00:19:38.720 --> 00:19:41.678
- Actually, it's never really been...
- Like this.

00:19:43.480 --> 00:19:47.359
- That's because I never really liked you.
- True. Makes things easier.

00:20:05.680 --> 00:20:08.069
Do you need to stretch
so you won't pull a hammy?

00:20:08.240 --> 00:20:11.312
- Or are you ready for your workout?
- I'm sorry, Summer.

00:20:11.480 --> 00:20:15.109
I need to take a stand. This separation
of the public and private spheres...

00:20:15.280 --> 00:20:17.999
...isn't working for me. I can't do it.
- But I told you how...

00:20:18.160 --> 00:20:20.355
One day you might have
some MTV-driven radio hits...

00:20:20.520 --> 00:20:22.476
...and then a moderately priced
clothing line.

00:20:22.640 --> 00:20:27.031
I could get offered $20 million to portray
a blind superhero in a red leather unitard.

00:20:27.200 --> 00:20:31.079
But until then, as long as we're
complete faceless nobodies...

00:20:31.240 --> 00:20:32.912
...living in obscurity...

00:20:33.800 --> 00:20:37.031
...I can't acknowledge you privately
if you won't acknowledge me publicly.

00:20:37.200 --> 00:20:39.919
Let me know when you're ready
to come to the bargaining table.

00:20:40.080 --> 00:20:41.911
Until then, just consider me on strike.

00:20:42.080 --> 00:20:44.071
You'll cross your own picket line
in no time.

00:20:44.240 --> 00:20:45.992
Fight the power.

00:20:51.440 --> 00:20:54.000
- Eddie.
- Hey.

00:20:54.160 --> 00:20:57.596
- Hey, man.
- How's it going, Ryan? Good to see you.

00:20:58.520 --> 00:21:00.238
You look good.

00:21:00.400 --> 00:21:02.072
You look good, man.

00:21:02.240 --> 00:21:04.959
Yeah, I went up and visited
your brother last week.

00:21:05.120 --> 00:21:07.918
It kills me he's still serving time.

00:21:08.160 --> 00:21:11.596
- Sucks, huh?
- Yeah. Yeah.

00:21:11.760 --> 00:21:14.593
It's been a while, man.
What are you doing here?

00:21:14.760 --> 00:21:17.479
Well, actually...

00:21:18.080 --> 00:21:19.433
...I'm looking for Theresa.

00:21:19.760 --> 00:21:20.988
Theresa?

00:21:21.160 --> 00:21:25.551
Yeah, you know, her mom said
she was working out here in Newport...

00:21:25.720 --> 00:21:29.679
...and your brother said you were living
the life out here, you know, so I...

00:21:29.840 --> 00:21:33.310
- I thought maybe you'd seen her.
- She didn't leave a note or something?

00:21:34.560 --> 00:21:35.879
No.

00:21:36.040 --> 00:21:37.553
Nothing.

00:21:37.960 --> 00:21:40.679
Some thanks for the ring I got her, huh?

00:21:40.840 --> 00:21:43.877
- Ring?
- Yeah, we're engaged.

00:21:44.880 --> 00:21:46.108
Engaged?

00:21:49.280 --> 00:21:51.555
Damn, Eddie, that's great, man.

00:21:51.760 --> 00:21:53.512
Yeah. Yeah, it is.

00:21:55.920 --> 00:21:57.512
So she...

00:21:57.680 --> 00:22:00.114
I mean, she hasn't looked you up at all?

00:22:00.280 --> 00:22:02.475
No, sorry.

00:22:07.120 --> 00:22:11.193
- You're living the dream out here, huh?
- Yeah, you said it.

00:22:11.360 --> 00:22:12.952
That's all right. You deserve it.

00:22:13.400 --> 00:22:15.868
You know, putting up with Trey
for all those years.

00:22:20.680 --> 00:22:24.070
All right.
I'm gonna get out of here.

00:22:24.240 --> 00:22:25.434
But...

00:22:28.520 --> 00:22:32.229
- Hey, if you see her, you know, just...
- Yeah.

00:22:37.360 --> 00:22:39.430
I don't know, I just...

00:22:39.600 --> 00:22:42.398
I can't believe she'd
run out on me like that.

00:22:44.240 --> 00:22:45.434
Neither can I.

00:22:51.400 --> 00:22:53.960
- Were you gonna tell me you're engaged?
- I'm not engaged.

00:22:54.120 --> 00:22:57.476
- What the hell are you doing?
- He asked, I didn't say yes.

00:22:57.640 --> 00:23:00.200
- So you took off. That'll fix everything?
- You did.

00:23:01.760 --> 00:23:03.432
Sorry.

00:23:03.840 --> 00:23:06.070
You're gonna have to face him
sooner or later.

00:23:06.240 --> 00:23:09.277
- I just need time to think.
- Yeah, you need about five years.

00:23:09.440 --> 00:23:11.795
- You're 17.
- What's gonna be different in five years?

00:23:11.960 --> 00:23:14.110
Or have you forgotten
where you come from?

00:23:14.280 --> 00:23:16.953
Not everybody has an infinity pool,
goes to private school...

00:23:17.120 --> 00:23:19.395
...and drives a Range Rover.
- What are you saying?

00:23:19.560 --> 00:23:23.314
Eddie has his own place, he's a foreman at
work and isn't a screwup like his friends.

00:23:23.480 --> 00:23:26.119
- All good reasons to marry him.
- And he loves me.

00:23:28.720 --> 00:23:31.234
- And you?
- I just need time.

00:23:41.680 --> 00:23:44.148
- What are you doing for dinner?
- Nothing.

00:23:44.360 --> 00:23:47.033
- Don't say you're not hungry.
- I didn't say I wasn't hungry.

00:23:47.240 --> 00:23:49.549
I'm starving.
Why do you think I'm being a bitch?

00:23:49.960 --> 00:23:52.838
What are you gonna do, eat out of
the vending machine? Come on.

00:23:53.000 --> 00:23:54.752
Come on.
Come to my house with me.

00:23:55.720 --> 00:23:57.676
You just need a ride.

00:23:58.640 --> 00:24:00.596
Upstairs, alone. Now.

00:24:00.760 --> 00:24:04.514
Upstairs alone? I'm afraid I'd have to
file a grievance with the union.

00:24:04.680 --> 00:24:06.671
- I've had enough.
- I left you two hours ago.

00:24:06.840 --> 00:24:09.798
Well, it feels like four.
I've been thinking about what you said...

00:24:09.960 --> 00:24:13.350
...and I find it totally insensitive.
- I'm being insensitive? Really? How?

00:24:13.520 --> 00:24:16.717
Can't you accept that I'm uncomfortable
with public displays of affection?

00:24:17.000 --> 00:24:19.560
You're offering yourself for $ 10 a pop
at a kissing booth.

00:24:19.720 --> 00:24:22.678
How much more publicly
can affection be displayed?

00:24:22.840 --> 00:24:26.674
I know there's a strike,
but technically...

00:24:26.840 --> 00:24:30.276
...you wouldn't be considered a scab...
- Summer, don't say "scab."

00:24:30.800 --> 00:24:32.677
If you didn't have to do anything.

00:24:36.360 --> 00:24:38.749
Well, your strike-busting techniques
are no good here.

00:24:38.920 --> 00:24:41.912
Sorry, the rank and file
are holding strong.

00:24:42.880 --> 00:24:44.359
Solidarity.

00:24:46.920 --> 00:24:48.114
Cal.

00:24:48.720 --> 00:24:50.756
- What a surprise.
- A welcome one, I hope.

00:24:50.920 --> 00:24:53.878
Well, that depends.

00:24:54.040 --> 00:24:56.349
You've brought flowers?

00:24:59.200 --> 00:25:01.031
Thank you. They're beautiful.

00:25:01.200 --> 00:25:03.395
- I missed you.
- I've missed you too.

00:25:03.560 --> 00:25:07.269
Neither of us are love-struck adolescents
looking to be swept off our feet.

00:25:07.440 --> 00:25:11.399
We're both adults. Our lives
are full of responsibilities, difficulties.

00:25:11.560 --> 00:25:13.391
Well, isn't this romantic.

00:25:13.560 --> 00:25:15.710
We should be able
to come to some arrangement...

00:25:15.880 --> 00:25:18.838
...where we both get from a relationship
what we want.

00:25:19.560 --> 00:25:21.915
Is this a booty call?

00:25:22.240 --> 00:25:23.878
What's a booty call?

00:25:24.040 --> 00:25:27.032
It's when you show up at night,
unannounced, no apologies...

00:25:27.200 --> 00:25:29.714
...no compliments, no commitments...

00:25:29.880 --> 00:25:33.156
...just some crappy mini-carns
from Ralphs...

00:25:33.320 --> 00:25:35.515
...and a very mistaken idea
that I just might wanna...

00:25:45.040 --> 00:25:46.519
Guess it was a booty call.

00:25:46.680 --> 00:25:49.148
How much are you involved
with Uncle Shaun, day-to-day?

00:25:50.320 --> 00:25:51.719
Not much.

00:25:51.880 --> 00:25:53.996
He spends most of his time
out of the office...

00:25:54.160 --> 00:25:56.276
...on site with the crews,
suppliers, inspectors.

00:25:56.440 --> 00:25:59.716
You gotta be a hard-ass to be good
at that job. Lots of tough characters.

00:26:00.360 --> 00:26:03.079
I'm sure Shaun can be persuasive
when he needs to be.

00:26:03.240 --> 00:26:05.993
Convincing-argument persuasive,
or baseball-bat persuasive?

00:26:06.160 --> 00:26:10.472
If you don't wanna help him, I understand.
I didn't think you'd do it in the first place.

00:26:10.640 --> 00:26:14.952
Hey, dinner's ready.
Slaved over hot take-out containers.

00:26:15.120 --> 00:26:17.076
- Ryan here?
- Hey.

00:26:18.400 --> 00:26:20.197
- This is Theresa.
- Hi.

00:26:20.360 --> 00:26:22.351
- Hello, friend.
- Nice to meet you.

00:26:22.520 --> 00:26:24.272
I'm Kirsten. And this is...

00:26:24.440 --> 00:26:27.238
Sandy. Hi.
I've heard so much about you.

00:26:27.400 --> 00:26:29.834
It's nice to meet you all.
Can I help? It looks great.

00:26:30.000 --> 00:26:34.596
Sure. The key is taking the food
out of the Styrofoam containers.

00:26:34.760 --> 00:26:36.591
But her real specialty is ordering.

00:26:36.760 --> 00:26:38.990
Is the silverware in the drawer or...?

00:26:39.160 --> 00:26:42.596
What's going on? Don't say "nothing,"
because it's not nothing. It's something.

00:26:42.760 --> 00:26:45.399
- She's engaged.
- Wow. You make quick work of the ladies.

00:26:45.600 --> 00:26:48.160
- To this guy Eddie.
- Oh, she just told you?

00:26:48.320 --> 00:26:51.392
No, he did, when he showed up
looking for her.

00:26:54.920 --> 00:26:56.114
What's going on here?

00:26:56.280 --> 00:26:59.636
- And don't say "nothing."
- Because it's not nothing. It's something.

00:26:59.800 --> 00:27:01.995
What we have here
is our very own <i>telenovela</i>.

00:27:02.160 --> 00:27:04.720
- <i>Telenovela</i>?
- Yeah. Spanish-language soap opera.

00:27:04.880 --> 00:27:08.395
<i>Ni��a Amada M��a</i>.
I hope Isabela gets Victor.

00:27:08.560 --> 00:27:09.959
I love his handlebar moustache.

00:27:10.440 --> 00:27:12.032
- You do it.
- Give it to me.

00:27:15.880 --> 00:27:18.553
<i>Previously on</i> The Valley<i>:</i>

00:27:20.760 --> 00:27:22.432
Hey.

00:27:22.800 --> 00:27:26.110
What are you doing home?
I thought you'd be over at Ryan's house.

00:27:26.280 --> 00:27:29.238
He's kind of busy.
A friend from home.

00:27:29.400 --> 00:27:32.551
- Theresa.
- And you're okay with that?

00:27:32.720 --> 00:27:35.280
- Yeah. It's not a big deal.
- It is kind of a big deal.

00:27:35.440 --> 00:27:37.635
- He's important to you.
- What's important to me...

00:27:37.800 --> 00:27:41.554
...is that we not talk about this right now,
because I'm fine.

00:27:42.040 --> 00:27:44.759
It's just high school.

00:27:45.600 --> 00:27:48.512
Hey, that's supposed to be my line, okay?
You're supposed to say...

00:27:48.680 --> 00:27:52.468
...I could never understand. And how Ryan
is the most important thing in the world...

00:27:52.640 --> 00:27:55.279
...and without him...
- We're just friends.

00:27:55.440 --> 00:27:59.399
- Or at least we're trying to be.
- Look, at the risk of embarrassing you...

00:27:59.560 --> 00:28:01.357
...you and Ryan...

00:28:02.040 --> 00:28:04.110
...never friends.
- So I've been told.

00:28:04.280 --> 00:28:07.670
- But if we can't be friends, then...
- Let him know what you wanna be.

00:28:09.200 --> 00:28:11.873
See? There's still room around here
for me to be the adult.

00:28:12.040 --> 00:28:13.758
Okay?

00:28:16.280 --> 00:28:18.589
So we're all dressed up
for my brother's 16th birthday.

00:28:18.760 --> 00:28:22.719
Not this one. Don't you have anything
that doesn't involve me falling down?

00:28:22.880 --> 00:28:25.314
Did Ryan fall down when he did musicals?
Tell us.

00:28:25.480 --> 00:28:29.189
You did musicals?
I did a musical or two myself in college.

00:28:29.360 --> 00:28:32.352
Someone stop him before he starts
singing "Greased Lightnin'."

00:28:32.520 --> 00:28:34.112
Do it, Dad. Travolta's your bitch.

00:28:34.280 --> 00:28:35.918
- Thank you, son.
- Go ahead.

00:28:36.080 --> 00:28:38.469
We were at the Holiday Inn,
at the revolving restaurant...

00:28:38.640 --> 00:28:41.632
...and Ryan has this thing about heights...
- I'll get it.

00:28:41.800 --> 00:28:43.392
Excuse me.

00:28:46.320 --> 00:28:48.550
- Hey, sweetie.
- Hey.

00:28:48.720 --> 00:28:51.154
- Is Ryan here?
- Yes, he is.

00:28:51.320 --> 00:28:53.629
- I love revolving restaurants.
- Who doesn't?

00:28:53.800 --> 00:28:56.030
Motion and digestion,
unbeatable combination.

00:28:57.120 --> 00:28:58.792
Look who's here.

00:28:59.840 --> 00:29:01.831
- Hey.
- Hey.

00:29:05.000 --> 00:29:07.070
Does everybody know everybody?

00:29:07.240 --> 00:29:09.629
- Yeah. Hi, Theresa.
- Hi, Marissa.

00:29:11.720 --> 00:29:15.235
- You hungry?
- Actually, I'm starved. Is it okay?

00:29:15.400 --> 00:29:17.231
- Sure.
- Absolutely. Have a seat.

00:29:17.400 --> 00:29:19.914
Let me get you a plate.

00:29:27.920 --> 00:29:30.673
So, what's everyone talking about?

00:29:38.240 --> 00:29:41.118
Hey, man, phone for you.
It's Eddie.

00:29:45.360 --> 00:29:48.511
Hey, man, I can't find him.
Do you want me to take a message?

00:29:48.760 --> 00:29:50.637
Apparently not. He hung up.

00:29:50.800 --> 00:29:55.112
So dinner last night,
entertaining for the rest of us...

00:29:55.320 --> 00:29:57.550
...but for you, wow.
- What, last night?

00:29:57.720 --> 00:30:00.553
The whole dinner-theater/<i>telenovela</i> thing
you performed.

00:30:00.720 --> 00:30:03.359
- <i>Telenovela?</i>
- Yeah, Spanish-language sudser.

00:30:03.520 --> 00:30:05.829
Telemundo, dude. Univision.

00:30:06.000 --> 00:30:07.911
Victor, with the sexy
handlebar moustache.

00:30:10.080 --> 00:30:13.311
So you still have the mindset
that you're the friend guy, huh?

00:30:13.480 --> 00:30:16.040
Befriending any beautiful woman
who cares to dine with us?

00:30:16.200 --> 00:30:19.397
- I'm working on it.
- Right. Well, if I may...

00:30:19.560 --> 00:30:22.120
...speaking from
a recent personal experience...

00:30:22.680 --> 00:30:26.514
...the triangle's not a friendly shape,
okay? It's pointy. It's got sharp edges.

00:30:26.680 --> 00:30:28.636
- Triangles hurt people.
- There's no triangle.

00:30:28.800 --> 00:30:30.950
Marissa and I aren't together.
Theresa's here for work.

00:30:31.120 --> 00:30:33.509
Except Marissa still obviously
has feelings for you...

00:30:33.680 --> 00:30:36.114
...and Theresa obviously
has feelings for you.

00:30:36.280 --> 00:30:40.068
In fact, the only thing that's not obvious
is how Ryan Atwood feels.

00:30:41.520 --> 00:30:43.795
- I don't know. It's complicated.
- It is complicated.

00:30:43.960 --> 00:30:47.191
It's complicated by the fact that
there's an Eddie who still obviously...

00:30:47.360 --> 00:30:50.955
...has feelings for Theresa. That would
actually make this romantic triangle...

00:30:51.120 --> 00:30:54.396
...more of a romantic rhombus.
- So, what am I supposed to do?

00:30:54.560 --> 00:30:57.233
That I don't know.
But I would do something soon...

00:30:57.400 --> 00:30:59.436
...otherwise someone's gonna get hurt.

00:31:00.400 --> 00:31:03.233
Judging from Eddie's phone voice,
it's probably gonna be you.

00:31:04.080 --> 00:31:05.798
<i>What the hell do you expect, Sandy?</i>

00:31:06.360 --> 00:31:09.989
Construction's a dirty business.
Bids accepted below cost.

00:31:10.160 --> 00:31:12.674
Permits mysteriously approved
at the last second.

00:31:12.840 --> 00:31:15.912
Guys like Shaun
are the lifeblood of the industry.

00:31:16.520 --> 00:31:19.398
Well, that was a touching speech, Cal,
but still the answer's no.

00:31:19.760 --> 00:31:21.273
Good luck.

00:31:21.440 --> 00:31:25.672
You're opening a Pandora's box,
you know that? Shaun's old. He's tired.

00:31:25.880 --> 00:31:28.838
If the DA starts asking questions,
he's got lots of answers.

00:31:29.000 --> 00:31:32.231
If you build your empire on quicksand,
sooner or later it's gonna sink.

00:31:32.400 --> 00:31:35.119
What about Kirsten?
She's complicit in all this too.

00:31:35.280 --> 00:31:38.397
- She doesn't know anything about this.
- Because I didn't tell her.

00:31:38.560 --> 00:31:41.597
I was trying to protect her.
But she's number two at Newport Group.

00:31:41.760 --> 00:31:43.910
She signs Shaun's paychecks.

00:31:44.080 --> 00:31:46.799
So like it or not,
we're in this mess together.

00:31:56.560 --> 00:31:57.913
Hey.

00:31:58.080 --> 00:31:59.718
Hi.

00:32:01.560 --> 00:32:04.870
Look, I'm sorry, okay?

00:32:05.040 --> 00:32:08.999
It's not like Cohen and I planned to
get together. It sort of just happened.

00:32:09.160 --> 00:32:12.152
And if it makes you feel better,
I don't think it's gonna work out.

00:32:12.880 --> 00:32:15.269
Well, that makes me feel great.

00:32:19.280 --> 00:32:22.352
I just can't be like one of those
couples, you know...

00:32:22.520 --> 00:32:25.353
...who hold hands in the hallway
and make out in between classes.

00:32:25.520 --> 00:32:27.795
Let the whole world
know what's going on.

00:32:27.960 --> 00:32:30.315
It's none of their business, you know?

00:32:30.560 --> 00:32:32.232
You don't have to ignore him, Summer.

00:32:32.400 --> 00:32:33.958
I don't ignore him.

00:32:34.120 --> 00:32:36.395
Okay, maybe a little,
but only in public.

00:32:36.560 --> 00:32:38.835
You spent so much time
trying to get his attention.

00:32:39.000 --> 00:32:40.877
I mean, you dressed up
as Wonder Woman.

00:32:41.520 --> 00:32:44.080
Well, Wonder Woman
is supposed to have an invisible jet...

00:32:44.680 --> 00:32:47.240
...not an invisible boyfriend.

00:32:48.440 --> 00:32:51.830
I mean, either you're really evil
or there's something else going on.

00:32:54.680 --> 00:32:56.989
I just don't know why he likes me.

00:32:57.360 --> 00:33:00.636
I mean, he's way smarter. And we have,
like, less than nothing in common.

00:33:00.800 --> 00:33:04.031
And he's just gonna get bored with me,
because, pretty much, all boys do.

00:33:04.560 --> 00:33:05.993
If everybody knows we're dating...

00:33:06.160 --> 00:33:08.674
...they'll know when he breaks up
with me, which he will.

00:33:11.680 --> 00:33:14.797
I mean, dumped by Seth Cohen?

00:33:14.960 --> 00:33:17.315
It's real good for my reputation.

00:33:20.560 --> 00:33:22.755
- Hello?
- <i>Luke.</i>

00:33:23.040 --> 00:33:26.828
- Hey, Mrs...
- Do not say my name out loud.

00:33:27.000 --> 00:33:29.275
Come to the motel.
Park across the street and walk.

00:33:29.440 --> 00:33:31.954
I'll get the same room.
Knock twice so I know it's you.

00:33:32.200 --> 00:33:33.189
<i>And, Luke...</i>

00:33:33.880 --> 00:33:35.108
...this is a booty call.

00:33:40.640 --> 00:33:44.030
It turns out you're not the only one
who's a coward.

00:33:44.240 --> 00:33:47.277
- Oh, it's nice to see you also, yeah?
- Summer's scared too.

00:33:47.440 --> 00:33:49.635
I know. She's scared to be seen
in public with me.

00:33:49.800 --> 00:33:52.473
Come on, Cohen. She fought for you.
She was fearless.

00:33:52.680 --> 00:33:55.877
Ruthless, in fact.
Now she's got you.

00:33:56.080 --> 00:33:57.798
There's nothing scarier than that.

00:33:58.240 --> 00:34:01.437
Nothing scarier than being with me,
or do you mean, like, anyone?

00:34:01.600 --> 00:34:03.909
Look, once you get what you want...

00:34:04.080 --> 00:34:05.991
...that's when you've got
something to lose.

00:34:06.240 --> 00:34:08.117
She's afraid of losing you, Cohen.

00:34:08.280 --> 00:34:09.952
Why? I'm not going anywhere.

00:34:10.240 --> 00:34:11.878
Maybe you need to let her know that.

00:34:36.360 --> 00:34:38.476
- Hi.
- Hey.

00:34:38.640 --> 00:34:41.200
Can we talk?
I know it's weird, me being here...

00:34:41.360 --> 00:34:45.194
...but I just really needed to know...
- Am I still in love with Ryan?

00:34:47.040 --> 00:34:48.632
Because you still are.

00:34:49.040 --> 00:34:50.712
I don't wanna be.

00:34:50.880 --> 00:34:53.838
It would be a whole lot easier
if I wasn't.

00:35:20.400 --> 00:35:22.550
- Hey, man. What's up?
- Hey.

00:35:24.640 --> 00:35:26.790
It's a long drive just to come say hello.

00:35:27.520 --> 00:35:29.875
Last night, when you asked me
about Theresa...

00:35:30.040 --> 00:35:32.156
...I wasn't completely honest.

00:35:34.680 --> 00:35:36.238
Carl.

00:35:36.840 --> 00:35:39.559
- I'm gonna take a break, all right?
- Okay.

00:35:49.480 --> 00:35:52.677
- So why lie?
- I'm sorry, man. I didn't...

00:35:53.400 --> 00:35:56.551
- She staying with you?
- No. She's working, like her mom said.

00:35:58.680 --> 00:36:00.591
Still, I...

00:36:00.760 --> 00:36:03.115
I mean, I pop the question...

00:36:03.280 --> 00:36:05.157
...and she runs away...

00:36:06.280 --> 00:36:08.077
...to you.

00:36:08.840 --> 00:36:10.637
Married?

00:36:11.280 --> 00:36:14.636
- Wow.
- Yeah, that's the plan.

00:36:15.280 --> 00:36:17.589
You must really love him a lot.

00:36:18.880 --> 00:36:20.074
<i>Do you love her?</i>

00:36:21.960 --> 00:36:24.394
- I don't know.
- Yeah, well, I do.

00:36:24.560 --> 00:36:26.232
Okay? I do.

00:36:26.400 --> 00:36:28.994
And I wanna take care of her.
Do you?

00:36:29.160 --> 00:36:30.798
I mean, can you?

00:36:31.760 --> 00:36:34.433
Look, I know this is tough. L...

00:36:35.840 --> 00:36:38.274
I can't tell you what to do.

00:36:39.160 --> 00:36:41.549
But if you wanted to,
you could talk to her.

00:36:41.720 --> 00:36:43.676
You know, convince her to come home.

00:36:43.840 --> 00:36:47.719
Otherwise, be ready to fight for her,
because I'm not just gonna walk away.

00:36:47.880 --> 00:36:49.518
I can't.

00:36:52.800 --> 00:36:55.075
You got a long ride home.

00:36:56.320 --> 00:36:57.639
You got a lot to think about.

00:37:02.120 --> 00:37:05.032
In the church where my mom goes,
there's a stained glass window...

00:37:05.200 --> 00:37:06.952
...of Teresa of Avila.

00:37:07.720 --> 00:37:09.995
Her heart's being pierced
by the arrow of an angel.

00:37:11.080 --> 00:37:12.399
Her eyes are closed.

00:37:12.880 --> 00:37:15.474
And even though it hurts her
to love that much...

00:37:15.640 --> 00:37:17.358
...she has the most beautiful smile.

00:37:20.160 --> 00:37:22.037
I remember my first communion.

00:37:22.200 --> 00:37:24.350
I was wearing a white dress and gloves.

00:37:24.520 --> 00:37:27.080
<i>And I looked up at that window</i>
<i>and I thought...</i>

00:37:27.240 --> 00:37:29.959
<i>... someday someone</i>
<i>would pierce my heart...</i>

00:37:31.040 --> 00:37:34.077
...and I would walk down the aisle
in a real white dress...

00:37:34.240 --> 00:37:36.071
...and understand why she's smiling.

00:37:42.640 --> 00:37:44.073
I know it sounds lame.

00:37:47.800 --> 00:37:50.473
But I guess life's not really like that.

00:37:51.640 --> 00:37:54.916
You can't get caught up in wishing
for something that's not gonna happen.

00:37:55.440 --> 00:37:58.159
You gotta hold on to the next best thing.

00:38:04.400 --> 00:38:06.630
I guess I should call Eddie.

00:38:07.120 --> 00:38:09.953
Yeah.
I should get back to school.

00:38:18.200 --> 00:38:19.428
So thanks.

00:38:19.760 --> 00:38:22.320
I can see why Ryan likes it here.

00:38:35.600 --> 00:38:38.478
Here you go. Full refund.
Thanks for coming. The show's over.

00:38:38.640 --> 00:38:40.710
Thanks so much, though.
It was great having you.

00:38:40.880 --> 00:38:43.348
- This kid bothering you, Summer?
- No, it's okay. Thanks.

00:38:43.520 --> 00:38:45.033
- Thanks.
- You're making a scene.

00:38:45.200 --> 00:38:47.077
- I need to talk to you.
- I'll IM you later.

00:38:48.120 --> 00:38:49.792
Okay.

00:38:54.120 --> 00:38:55.712
- Let's talk up here.
- Oh, my God. No.

00:38:56.120 --> 00:38:58.156
- Summer, I know you're scared.
- Yeah, of you.

00:38:58.320 --> 00:39:01.517
You kiss these other guys, but you won't
kiss me? Acknowledge me now...

00:39:01.680 --> 00:39:03.875
...or lose me forever.
- You're dating this emo geek?

00:39:04.040 --> 00:39:06.315
Yes, Brad, she's dating this emo geek.

00:39:06.480 --> 00:39:10.473
Yeah, that's right. I'm a big dork
and I listen to emo. And I'm dating her.

00:39:10.640 --> 00:39:14.474
- Why are you doing this?
- Because, Summer, I like you this much.

00:39:14.680 --> 00:39:17.433
And if you don't feel
the same way about me, then...

00:39:17.880 --> 00:39:20.599
Someone will have to give me
a hand down. It's high up here...

00:39:20.760 --> 00:39:23.911
...and I could fall and that would be
embarrassing. More embarrassing.

00:39:42.880 --> 00:39:44.598
I can't believe this.

00:39:44.760 --> 00:39:48.116
It's all over but the big,
public make-out session.

00:40:00.640 --> 00:40:02.153
That'll be 10 bucks, Cohen.

00:40:02.320 --> 00:40:04.550
That's for a worthy cause.

00:40:06.760 --> 00:40:09.035
Hey, Carl, can I talk to Eddie?

00:40:09.200 --> 00:40:12.078
Yeah. Yeah, I'll hold on.

00:40:20.600 --> 00:40:22.397
- Hi.
- Hey.

00:40:22.560 --> 00:40:23.754
You packing?

00:40:25.120 --> 00:40:26.599
Yeah.

00:40:27.280 --> 00:40:29.589
I think I should probably go home.

00:40:29.760 --> 00:40:32.354
Seems like the right thing to do, right?

00:40:32.960 --> 00:40:36.635
You gotta do what's right for you.
You and Eddie.

00:40:36.800 --> 00:40:39.360
I gotta figure out what's right for me...

00:40:39.520 --> 00:40:40.839
...and Marissa.

00:40:41.560 --> 00:40:43.118
Right.

00:40:46.000 --> 00:40:48.673
So if it's the right thing to do,
why don't I want you to go?

00:40:50.800 --> 00:40:52.870
Why don't I wanna go?

00:41:00.160 --> 00:41:02.276
I can think of a reason.

00:41:13.680 --> 00:41:15.272
<i>Hello?</i>

00:41:15.600 --> 00:41:17.192
<i>Hello?</i>

00:41:17.520 --> 00:41:19.272
<i>Theresa, are you there?</i>

00:41:19.640 --> 00:41:21.392
<i>Theresa?</i>

00:00:0.500 --> 00:00:2.00
